{{Expand German|Limes Mauretaniae|date=January 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{RomanMilitary}} The '''Limes Mauretaniae''' was a [[Roman Empire|Roman]] frontier territory in [[Africa]] and a defense line approximately 100 kilometers south of the modern day [[Algiers]].<ref name="Frank1959">{{cite book|author=Tenney Frank|title=An Economic Survey of Ancient Rome|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oVBoAAAAMAAJ|year=1959|publisher=Pageant Books|page=68}}</ref>
It was part of the North-African borderline between the Atlantic coast and the [[Limes Tripolitanus]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=René Ployer|author2=Marinus Polak|author3=Ricarda Schmidt|title=The frontiers of the Roman Empire: a thematic study and proposed world heritage nomination strategy|url=http://www.limeswerelderfgoed.nl/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/FRE-TS_FinalVersion_rapport_1.pdf|date=2017|access-date=25 January 2018}}</ref>
