{{Other uses|Yusuf and Zulaikha}}
[[Image:Yusufzulaikha1876.jpg|thumb|A miniature [[Mughal painting]] depicting the tale of Yusuf and Zulaikha]]

'''''Yusuf-Zulekha''''' ({{lang-bn|ইউসুফ-জুলেখা}}) is a 15th-century [[Bengali language|Bengali]] [[Romance (love)|romantic story]] in [[Verse (poetry)|verse]] written by [[Shah Muhammad Sagir]], which is considered one of the greatest literary works of medieval "golden era" of [[Bengali literature]]; when Sagir was a court-poet of [[Sultan]] [[Ghiyasuddin Azam Shah]] of [[Gaura]]. Sagir wrote the story on requested ny the Sultan.<ref name="Banglapedia">{{cite book |last1=Ahmed |first1=Wakil |authorlink1=Wakil Ahmed |editor=[[Sirajul Islam]] |title=Banglapedia |url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Yusuf-Zulekha |accessdate=December 14, 2015 |edition= |publication-date=January 2003 |publisher=[[Asiatic Society of Bangladesh]] |location=[[Dhaka]] |isbn=984-32-0576-6 |chapter=Yusuf-Zulekha}}</ref> 

